cs.CL, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on applying CHR to computational linguistics and grammar development tools. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of CHR in SICStus Prolog. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as CHR is a popular technique in AI for solving constraint satisfaction problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of CHR for handling complex constraints in HPSG, which is a popular linguistic theory used in natural language processing and machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the development of a grammar development system using CHR.
